rComments: It's actually concerning how many ppl found him caring, he literally yelled at one student at the very first midterm for asking if the camera setup okay. He's rude and has very poor teaching skills. He overcomplicates EVERY topic and doesn't communicate very well.

He is a very nice and caring person but I did not like his teaching style. When explaining theory, he over complicates simple concepts and often goes on unnecessary tangents, leaving him no time to go over example problems. I ended up giving up and teaching myself with other resources by the end of the term which proved to be more productive.

I would like to start by saying I think he's very nice and understands what he is doing very well. That being said, I don't necessarily think he is a great instructor to learn from. His lessons are long and sometimes he over complicates things. I would not take again, but he is very nice!
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Lecture heavy', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: He is really nice and caring prof. He doesn't hesitate to give his time after the class ends. He did an extra review before finals. Answers emails quickly. If you have any questions, he solves them during his office hour or after class. He usually explains the theory which makes it easier to learn.

AWFUL PROF
He doesn't know how to teach and when he does he only goes through the theory without going through any challenging practice problems. He's not good at explaining things as he expects you to go through the course notes and learn most of the content on your own. 
He barely posts any practice problems or examples.
WOULD NOT RECOMMEND!

Teaches a math course like it is a biology class, meaning,  avoids or entirely skips over practice examples that are important and instead goes over theory which is irrelevant. Don't take this prof because you will regret it.

Passionate, accessible out of class, informative office hours and answers to questions. Skimmed some info during lectures and was up to the class to solve on our own because he would go deep with some concepts using ideas we did not yet understand. First introduction into multi-dimensional systems felt like we didn't have the fundamentals.

Course is graded by three exams, all MCs so no room for error or points awared to correct steps. He does explain concepts well but rushes through it - that's because this course is too packed. His exams are not aimed at tricking you and destroying your grades.

Does not know how to teach. Spends 99 percent of lecture time on explaining the theory and does not do any examples. Also expects students to self teach what he calls "extra course notes" which is where the actual test material comes from. All in all, avoid this professor and pick someone who can actually teach.
The bad course I ever take in my life

1. Cares: available for office hours every week and answers emails same day
2. He tries hard and cares about understanding, but teaching is a gift. You need a solid math background to piece the answer together
3. Tests are fair and closely follow class material, never tricky
Don't recommend. Focus on yourself, don't dwell over professor's downfalls

Very bad prof, he goes too quickly through lectures and his handwriting is horrible. He also has a bad attitude and doesn't accept criticism from anyone, he's too defensive. I would say take another prof, but actually all profs for this course are bad.
Not fair to students that did well on midterm 1 but did bad on midterm 2. My GPA has been destroyed by this prof, avoid him!

I did well in MAT1330 and felt very prepared for MAT1321, however in Dr.Gharouni's class he does not explain concepts and either rushes through lectures or only does a single question during an entire lecture period. He does not allow students to improve their mark and provides homework practice for only a limited time. Would suggest any other prof

Dr. Gharouni is one of the most genuine math profs I have ever had. Cares about his students. Although the contents are tough, he explains well, is very organized, interacts with the class, and really wants to see his students succeed. If you have the option to take his class, I highly recommend it.

Very passionate about his work and topics that relate to it. Hasnt been very fair with peoples questions and told us to figure out complex numbers on our own. We are being marked on only the midterms and final which are multiple choice. Wouldnt extend practice quizzes so people could see the questions closer to the midterm even though ungraded.

Prof Ali is new to UOttawa as a prof but IMO is great! I highly recommend you take him if you can! He is so organized and provides the best resources! He is very kind and easily approachable in office hours. He encourages participation and answers questions really well. He explains concepts well and all his evaluations were MC due to covid 19.

Prof Ali is a new prof here, and so far, he's been really fair and so caring. His lectures are straight forward, provides amazing resources, and his printing is really neat. He's so nice (not strict), and explains concepts thoroughly if you have problems. Overall, I'd recommend! All his evaluations are MC and open book, so that helps too! chill!
